  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes `1. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for "Salaries and Allowances" (w.e.f. 9-9-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10749&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the ^1[Salary, Allowances and`
  line `Pension] of Members of Parliament Act, 1954.`
  line
  line `(2) It shall come into force on the first day of June, 1954.`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (10750)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10750&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act,--`
  line
  line `(a) "committee" means a Committee of either House of Parliament, and includes a Joint`
  line `Committee of both Houses;`
  line
  line `^1[(aa) "dependent" means any of the following relatives of a deceased member, namely:--`
  line
  line `(i) a minor legitimate son, and an unmarried legitimate daughter and a widowed mother;`
  line or
  line
  line `(ii) if wholly dependent on the earnings of the member at the time of his death, a son or a`
  line `daughter who has attained the age of eighteen years and who is infirm; or`
  line
  line `(iii) if wholly or in part dependent on the earnings of the member at the time of his`
  line death,--
  line
  line `(a) the parent; or`
  line
  line `(b) a minor brother or an unmarried sister; or`
  line
  line `(c) a widowed daughter-in-law; or`
  line
  line `(d) a minor child of a pre-deceased son; or`
  line
  line `(e) a minor child of a pre-deceased daughter where no parent of the child is alive; or`
  line
  line `(f) the paternal grandparent if no parent of the member is alive; or`
  line
  line `(g) such other person as may be specified by the rules made under section 9 by the`
  line `Joint Committee;]`
  line
  line `(b) "member" means a member of either House of Parliament, ^2[but, save as otherwise`
  line `expressly provided in this Act, does not include]--`
  line
  line `(i) a Minister as defined in the Salaries and Allowances of Ministers Act, 1952 (58 of`
  line `1952); ^3***`
  line
  line `^4[(ii) a Leader of the Opposition as defined in the Salary and Allowances of Leaders of`
  line `Opposition in Parliament Act, 1977 (33 of 1977); and]`
  line
  line `^5[(iii)] an officer of Parliament as defined in the Salaries and Allowances of Officers of`
  line `Parliament Act, 1953 (20 of 1953);`
  line
  line `(c) "new member" means a member who takes his seat in either House of Parliament after the`
  line `commencement of this Act and includes a member who is re-elected or re-nominated;`
  line
  line `(d) "period of residence on duty" means the period during which a member resides at a place`
  line `where a session of a House of Parliament or a sitting of a committee is held or where any other`
  line `business connected with his duties as such member is transacted, for the purpose of attending such`
  line `session or sitting or for the purpose of attending to such other business, and includes--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of session of a House of Parliament, a period of such residence, not`
  line `exceeding three days, immediately preceding the commencement of the session and a period`
  line `of such residence, not exceeding three days, immediately succeeding the ^6[date on which the`
  line `House of Parliament is adjourned sine die or for a period exceeding seven days], and`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a sitting of a committee or any other business a period of such residence,`
  line `not exceeding two days, immediately preceding the commencement of the business of the`
  line `committee or other business and a period of such residence, not exceeding two days,`
  line `immediately succeeding the conclusion of the business of the committee or other business;`
  line
  line `Explanation.--A member who ordinarily resides at a place where a session of a House of`
  line `Parliament or a sitting of a committee is held or where any other business connected with his`
  line `duties as such member is transacted shall, for the duration of the session or sitting or the time`
  line `occupied for the transaction of other business (including the three or two days immediately`
  line `preceding or succeeding), be deemed to reside at such place for the purpose of attending such`
  line `session or sitting or, as the case may be, for the purpose of attending to such other business;`
  line
  line `(e) "term of office" means,--`
  line
  line `(a) in relation to a person who is a member at the commencement of this Act, the period`
  line `beginning with such commencement and ending with the date on which his seat becomes`
  line vacant;
  line
  line `^7[(b) in relation to a new member,--`
  line
  line `(i) where such new member is a member of the Council of States elected in a biennial`
  line `election, or nominated, to that House, the period beginning with the date of publication of`
  line `the notification in the Official Gazette notifying his name under section 71 of the`
  line `Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951); or`
  line
  line `(ii) where such new member is a member of the House of the People elected in a`
  line `general election held for the purpose of constituting a new House of the People, the`
  line `period beginning with the date of publication of the notification of the Election`
  line `Commission under section 73 of the said Act; or`
  line
  line `(iii) where such new member is a member of either House of Parliament elected in a`
  line `bye-election to that House or a member nominated to the House of the People, the period`
  line `beginning with the date of his election referred to in section 67A of the said Act or, as the`
  line `case may be, the date of his nomination,`
  line
  line `and ending with, in each such case, the date on which his seat becomes vacant.]`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2004, s. 2 (w.e.f. 9-1-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 55 of 1958, s. 2, for "but does not include" (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `3. The word "and" omitted by Act 33 of 1977, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-11-1977).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-1977).`
  line
  line `5. Sub-clause (ii) renumbered as sub-clause (iii) by s. 11, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-11-1977).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 55 of 1958, s. 2, for "end of the session" (w.e.f. 1-6-1954).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 105 of 1976, s. 4, for sub-clause (b) (w.e.f. 9-9-1970).`
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (10751)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Salaries and daily allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10751&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] A member shall be entitled to receive ^2[a salary at the`
  line `the rate of ^3[one lakh rupees] per mensem] during the whole of his term of office ^4[and subject to any`
  line `any rules made under this Act] ^5[an allowance at the rate of two thousand rupees for each day] during`
  line `any period of residence on duty:`
  line
  line `^6[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), the salary payable to Members of`
  line `Parliament under sub-section (1) shall be reduced by thirty per cent. For a period of one year`
  line `commencing from the 1st April, 2020, to meet the exigencies arising out of Corona Virus (COVID19) pandemic.]`
  line
  line `^7[Provided that no member shall be entitled to the aforesaid allowance unless he signs the register,`
  line `maintained for this purpose by the Secretariat of the House of the People or, as the case may be,`
  line `Council of States, on all the days (except intervening holidays for which no such signing is required)`
  line `of the session of the House for which the allowance is claimed.]`
  line
  line `^8[Provided further that the rates of salary specified in this section shall be applicable from the 18th`
  line `18th day of May, 2009.]`
  line
  line `^9[(2) The salary and daily allowance of members shall be increased after every five years`
  line `commencing from 1st April, 2023 on the basis of Cost Inflation Index provided under clause (v) of`
  line `Explanation to section 48 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).]`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 3 numbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 13 of 2018, s. 142 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 37 of 2010, s. 2, for "a salary at the rate of sixteen thousand rupees per mensem" (w.e.f. 1-10-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 142, for "fifty thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 55 of 1958, s. 3, for "plus" ((w.e.f. 1-6-1954).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 37 of 2010, s. 2, for "an allowance at the rate of one thousand rupees for each day" (w.e.f. 1-10-2010).`
  line
  line `6. Ins. by Act 19 of 2020, s. 2 (w.e.f. 7-4-2020).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 48 of 1993, s. 2 (w.e.f. 9-6-1993).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 37 of 2010, s. 2, for the second proviso (w.e.f. 1-10-2010).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 13 of 2018, s. 142 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (10752)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Travelling allowances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10752&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) There shall be paid to each member in respect of every journey`
  line `performed by him ^1[in India] for the purpose of attending a session of a House of Parliament or a`
  line `meeting of a committee or for the purpose of attending to any other business connected with his duties`
  line `as a member, from his usual place of residence to the place where the session or the meeting is to be`
  line `held or the other business is to be transacted and for the return journey from such place to his usual`
  line `place of residence--`
  line
  line `^2* * * * *`
  line
  line `(b) if the journey is performed by air, an amount equal to one ^3[***] air fare for each such`
  line journey;
  line
  line `(c) if the journey or any part thereof cannot be performed by rail or air--`
  line
  line `^4[(i) where the journey or any part thereof is performed by steamer, an amount equal to`
  line `one ^5*** fare (without diet) for the highest class in the steamer for each such journey or part`
  line `thereof, or, if there is no regular steamer service, such amount for each such journey or part`
  line `thereof as may be prescribed by rules made under section 9;]`
  line
  line `(ii) where the journey or any part thereof is performed by road, ^6[a road mileage at the`
  line `rate of sixteen rupees per kilometre] for each such journey or part thereof:`
  line
  line `^7[Provided that when Parliament is in session and the spouse of a Member, if any, performs such`
  line `journey or part thereof by road, unaccompanied by such Member, in respect of which such spouse has`
  line `been allowed to travel by air or partly by air and partly by rail from the usual place of residence of the`
  line `Member to Delhi or back under sub-section (2) of section 6B, the road mileage prescribed under this`
  line `sub-clause shall be allowed to such Member for such journey or part thereof, subject to the condition`
  line `that the total number of such journeys shall not exceed eight in a year]:`
  line
  line `^8[Provided further that where a member performs journey by road in Delhi from and to an`
  line `aerodrome, he shall be paid a minimum amount of one hundred and twenty rupees for each such`
  line journey.]
  line
  line `^9* * * * *`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of sub-clause (ii) of clause (c) of this sub-section, the expression`
  line `"journey" shall include the journey from and to the railway station, port or aerodrome to and from the`
  line `usual place of residence of the member or, as the case may be, the residence of the member at the place where the session of the House of Parliament or a meeting of the committee is to be held or`
  line `where any other business is to be transacted.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a member who performs a journey by`
  line `road between places connected by rail or steamer, either wholly or in part, may draw the mileage`
  line `allowance referred to in sub-clause (ii) of clause (c) of sub-section (1) in place of the travelling`
  line `allowance which would have been admissible to him if he had travelled by rail or steamer, as the case`
  line `may be.`
  line
  line `^10[Provided that the total amount of travelling allowance drawn by such member for the entire`
  line `journey shall not exceed the amount which would have been admissible to him had he performed such`
  line `journey by rail or by steamer, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided further that the first proviso shall be applicable to such journey only where the places of`
  line `the journey are connected by express, mail or superfast train:]`
  line
  line `^11[Provided also that the first proviso shall not be applicable to a member who, in the opinion of`
  line `the Chairman of the Council of States or, as the case may be, the Speaker of the House of the People,`
  line `is so incapacitated physically and cannot travel by air or train:]`
  line
  line `^12[Provided also that in case a member resides within a distance of three hundred kilometers from`
  line `Delhi, he or his spouse, for the journey performed by him by road, may draw the mileage allowance`
  line `referred to in sub-clause (ii) of clause (c) of sub-section (1) in place of the travelling allowance which`
  line `would have been admissible to him had he performed such journey by rail or by road, as the case may`
  line `be:`
  line
  line `Provided also that in case a member resides in the States of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam, Manipur,`
  line `Meghalaya, Mizoram, Nagaland, Sikkim or Tripura, he or his spouse may draw the mileage allowance`
  line `referred to in sub-clause (ii) of clause (c) of sub-section (1) for journey performed by him by road`
  line `from his residence in any of the said States to the nearest airport.]`
  line
  line `^13[(3) There shall be paid to a member in respect of a journey performed by him in the course of a`
  line `tour outside India undertaken in the discharge of his duties as such member, such travelling and daily`
  line `allowances as may be prescribed by rules made under section 9.]`
  line
  line `^14[(4) There shall be paid to a person--`
  line
  line `(a) who has been elected in a biennial election as a member of the Council of States but the`
  line `notification in the Official Gazette notifying his name under section 71 of the Representation of`
  line `the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951) has not been published in the Official Gazette; or`
  line
  line `(b) who has been elected as a member of the House of the People in a general election held`
  line `for the purpose of constituting a new House of the People but the notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette notifying his name under section 73 of the Representation of the People Act, 1951(43 of`
  line `1951) has not been published in the Official Gazette; or`
  line
  line `(c) who has been elected in a bye-election as a member of either House of Parliament or`
  line `nominated as a member to either House of Parliament,`
  line
  line `an amount equivalent to the fare in respect of every journey performed by him for coming to Delhi`
  line `before the publication of notification referred to in clause (a) or clause (b), or election or nomination`
  line `under clause (c):`
  line
  line `Provided that in case the journey is performed by rail or steamer or road, he shall be entitled to the`
  line `reimbursement of the fare or road mileage to which a member is entitled:`
  line
  line `Provided further that in case he performs the journey by air, such journey shall be included for the`
  line `purpose of counting thirty-two journeys referred to in the first proviso to sub-section (2) of section 5.]`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 1958, s. 4 (w.e.f. 1-4-1955).`
  line
  line `2. Clause (a) omitted by Act 13 of 2018, by s 143 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `3. The words "and one fourth of the" omitted by s. 143, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 55 of 1958, s. 4, for sub-clause (i) (w.e.f. 1-6-1954).`
  line
  line `5. The words "and three-fifth of the" omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 143 (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 37 of 2010, s. 3, "a road mileage at the rate of thirteen rupees per kilometer" (w.e.f. 1-10-2010).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for the first proviso (w.e.f. 1-10-2010).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by Act 48 of 1993, s. 3 (w.e.f. 9-6-1993).`
  line
  line `9. The third proviso omitted by Act 37 of 2010, s. 3 (w.e.f. 1-10-2010).`
  line
  line `10. Ins. by Act 17 of 2000, s. 2 (w.e.f. 7-6-2000).`
  line
  line `11. Ins. by Act 40 of 2006, s. 3 (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 9 of 2004, s. 3 (w.e.f. 9-1-2004).`
  line
  line `13. Ins. by Act 55 of 1958, s. 4 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `14. Ins. by Act 9 of 2004, s. 3 (w.e.f. 9-1-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (10753)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Travelling allowances for intermediate journeys.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10753&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `^1[(1)] Where a member absents himself`
  line `for less than fifteen days during a session of a House of Parliament or a sitting of a committee for`
  line `visiting any place in India, he shall be entitled to receive travelling allowances in respect of such`
  line `journey to such place and for the return journey--`
  line
  line `(a) if the journey is performed by rail, equal to ^2[one first class fare] for each such journey`
  line `irrespective of the class in which the member actually travels;`
  line
  line `(b)`
  line `^3[if the journey, being a journey during the sitting of the Committee] is performed by air,`
  line `equal to one fare by air for each such journey:`
  line
  line `Provided that such travelling allowances shall not exceed the total amount of daily allowances`
  line `which would have been admissible to such member under section 3 for the days of absence if he had`
  line `not so remained absent:]`
  line
  line `^4[Provided further that nothing in the first proviso shall apply, if the member performs the journey`
  line `by air for visiting any place in India not more than once during a sitting of the Committee;]`
  line
  line `^5[(1A) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (1), a member shall be entitled to`
  line `receive travelling allowances in respect of every journey performed by air for visiting any place in`
  line `India during the interval not exceeding ^6[five days] between two sittings of a Department related`
  line `Standing Committee when a House of Parliament is adjourned for a fixed period during the Budget`
  line `Session:`
  line
  line `Provided that such travelling allowances, excluding the air fare, shall not exceed the total amount`
  line `of daily allowances which would have been admissible to such member under section 3 for the days`
  line `of absence if he had not remained absent.]`
  line
  line `^7[(2) Every member shall be entitled to an amount equal to the fare by air for each single journey`
  line `by air (other than a journey referred to in section 4 or the second proviso to sub-section (1) of this`
  line `section or section 6C) performed by him ^8[either alone or along with spouse or any number of`
  line `companions or relatives,] from any place in India to any other place in India during his term of office`
  line `as such member:]`
  line
  line `^9[Provided that the total number of such journeys under this sub-section shall be thirty-four`
  line `journeys per year:`
  line
  line `^10[Provided further that where the number of journeys performed by any member by air is ^11[less`
  line `than thirty-four], then, such number of journeys not performed by him shall be carried over to the`
  line `following year:]`
  line
  line `^12[Provided also that the spouse or companion of a member, as the case may be, may alone`
  line `perform maximum eight journeys by air from any place of India to the place in India for the purpose`
  line `of visiting such member and such journey shall be included for the purpose of counting ^13[thirty-four`
  line `journeys] referred to in the first proviso to sub-section (2):]`
  line
  line `^14[Provided also that in case any member avails a total number of journeys by air more than thirtythirty-four, such journeys permissible to him, in the year, he may be allowed to adjust not exceeding`
  line `eight such journeys from the entitled number of journeys which may accrue in his credit in the next`
  line `following year.]`
  line
  line `^15[(3) Notwithstanding anything contained in sub-section (2), there shall be paid to a member who,`
  line `who, in the opinion of the Chairman of the Council of States or, as the case may be, the Speaker of`
  line `the House of the People, is so incapacitated physically and therefore cannot perform air or travel`
  line `journey, road mileage for the entire journey.]`
  line
  line `Explanation 1.--The provisions of clause (c) of sub-section (1) and sub-section (2) of section 4`
  line `shall, so far as may be, apply to travelling allowances payable under this section as they apply to`
  line `travelling allowances payable under that section.`
  line
  line `Explanation II.--For the purposes of this section, "year" means,--`
  line
  line `(i) in the case of a person who is a member at the commencement of the Salary, Allowances`
  line `and Pension of Members of Parliament (Amendment) Act, 1985 (74 of 1985), the year beginning`
  line `with such commencement and each of the subsequent years;`
  line
  line `(ii) in the case of a person who becomes a member after such commencement, the year`
  line `beginning with the date on which his term of office as such member commences and each of the`
  line `subsequent years.]]`
  line
  line `^16[Explanation III.--For the purposes of sub-section (2), any journey performed by the ^17["spouse,`
  line `companions or relatives shall be added in computing the limit of ^18[thirty-four journeys] specified in`
  line `the proviso to that sub-section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Section 5 renumbered as sub-section (1) of that section by Act 105 of 1976, s. 5 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 9 of 1955, s. 2, for "one second class fare" (w.e.f. 1-4-1955).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 74 of 1985, s. 3, for "if the journey" (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s. 3, ibid., for the second proviso and the Explanation (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 18 of 1995, s. 2 (w.e.f. 1-4-1995).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 40 of 2006, s. 4, for "seven days" (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 74 of 1985, s. 3, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 16 of 1999, s. 2, for "either alone or along with companion or spouse," (w.e.f. 18-3-1999).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by Act 40 of 2006, s. 4, for the first proviso (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
  line
  line `10. The proviso inserted by Act 28 of 1998, s. 4 (w.e.f. 20-8-1998).`
  line
  line `11. Subs. by Act 40 of 2006, s. 4, for "less than thirty-two" (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
  line
  line `12. Ins. by Act 9 of 2004, s. 4 (w.e.f. 9-1-2004).`
  line
  line `13. Subs. by Act 40 of 2006, s. 4, for "thirty-two journeys" (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
  line
  line `14. Ins. by Act 40 of 2006, s. 4 (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
  line
  line `15. Ins. by s. 4, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
  line
  line `16. Ins. by Act 3 of 1993, s. 2 (w.e.f. 5-1-1993).`
  line
  line `17. Subs. by Act 16 of 1999, s. 2, for "the companion or the spouse shall be added in computing the limit of twenty-eight`
  line `journeys specified in the proviso to that sub-section." (w.e.f. 18-3-1999).`
  line
  line `18. Subs. by Act 40 of 2006, s. 4, for "thirty-two journeys" (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_5_a:
  sectionId (10754)
  sectionNo 5A
  orderNo 6
  title `Transit accommodation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2004, s. 5 (w.e.f. 9-1-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10754&sectionno=5A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_5_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[5A. Transit accommodation.--Where a person referred to in sub-section (4) of section 4`
  line `comes to Delhi, he shall be entitled to such transit accommodation for such period as may be specified`
  line `by the rules made under clause (ccc) of sub-section (3) of section 9 by the Joint Committee.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (10755)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 7
  title `Free transit by Railway.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10755&sectionno=6&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `^1[6. Free transit by railway.--(1) Every member shall be provided with one free`
  line `non-transferable ^2[first class air-conditioned or executive class of any train] pass which shall entitle`
  line `him to travel at any time by any railway in India.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--^3[For the purposes of this sub-section and sections 6A and 6B], a member shall`
  line `include a Minister as defined in the Salaries and Allowances of Ministers Act, 1952 (58 of 1952), ^4[a`
  line `Leader of the Opposition as defined in the Salary and Allowances of Leader of Opposition in`
  line `Parliament Act, 1977 (33 of 1977)] and an officer of Parliament as defined in the Salaries and`
  line `Allowances of Officers of Parliament Act, 1953 (20 of 1953), other than the Chairman of the Council`
  line `of States.`
  line
  line `(2) A free railway pass issued to a member under sub-section (1) shall be valid for the term of his`
  line `office and on the expiration of such term, the pass shall be surrendered to the Secretary of the House`
  line `of the People or the Council of States, as the case may be:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such pass is issued to a new member before he takes his seat in either`
  line `House of Parliament, he shall be entitled to use the pass for attending a session of that House for`
  line `taking his seat therein.`
  line
  line `(3) Until a member is provided with a free railway pass under sub-section (1) he shall be, and`
  line `shall be deemed always to have been entitled to an amount equal to one ^5[first class air-conditioned or`
  line `or executive class of any train] fare for any journey of the nature referred to in sub-section (1) of`
  line `section 4 performed by him by rail.`
  line
  line `(4) A member who on ceasing to be a member surrenders his pass shall, if he performs any return`
  line `journey by rail of the nature referred to in sub-section (1) of section 4, be entitled and be deemed`
  line `always to have been entitled in respect of that journey to an amount equal to one ^5[first class airconditioned or executive class of any trains] fare.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall be construed as disentitling a member to any travelling`
  line `allowances to which he is otherwise entitled under the provisions of this Act.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1958, s. 5, for section 6 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 16 of 1999, s. 3, for "air-conditioned two tier" (w.e.f. 18-3-1999).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 29 of 1972, s. 3, for "For the purposes of this sub-section and section 6A" (w.e.f. 9-6-1972).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 33 of 1977, s. 11 (w.e.f. 1-11-1977).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by Act 16 of 1999, s. 3, for "air-conditioned two-tier" (w.e.f. 18-3-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a:
  sectionId (10756)
  sectionNo 6A
  orderNo 8
  title `Free transit by Steamer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10756&sectionno=6A&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[6A. Free transit by Steamer.--(1)`
  line `^2[Without prejudice to the provisions of section 6, every`
  line `member representing the Union territory of Andaman and Nicobar Islands or the Union territory of`
  line `Lakshadweep shall--`
  line
  line `(a) be provided with one free non-transferable pass which shall entitle him to travel at any`
  line `time by the highest class by steamer to and from any part of his constituency and any other part of`
  line `his constituency or the nearest part in the main land of India; and`
  line
  line `(b) be entitled to an amount equal to the fare by air from his usual place of residence to the`
  line `nearest airport in the main land of India ^3[and back]:]`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be construed as absolving the member from`
  line `payment of any diet charges payable by him during such travel.`
  line
  line `(2) A free steamer pass issued to a member under sub-section (1) shall be valid for the term of his`
  line `office and on the expiration of his term, the pass shall be surrendered to the Secretary of the House of`
  line `the People:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such pass is issued to a new member before he takes his seat in the`
  line `House of the People, he shall be entitled to use the pass for attending a session of that House for`
  line `taking his seat therein.`
  line
  line `(3) Until a member is provided with a free steamer pass under sub-section (1), he shall be entitled`
  line `to an amount equal to one fare (without diet) for the highest class for any journey of the nature`
  line `referred to in sub-section (1) of section 4 performed by him by steamer.`
  line
  line `(4) A member who on ceasing to be a member surrenders the steamer pass issued to him under`
  line `sub-section (1), shall, if he performs any return journey by steamer of the nature referred to in`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4, be entitled in respect of that journey to an amount equal to one fare`
  line `(without diet) for the highest class.`
  line
  line `(5) Nothing in this section shall be construed as disentitling a member to any travelling`
  line `allowances to which he is otherwise entitled under the provisions of this Act.`
  line
  line `(6) In addition to ^4[the facilities provided to a member] under sub-section (1), he shall also be`
  line entitled--
  line
  line `(i) to one free pass for one person to accompany the member and travel by the ^5[highest class]`
  line `class] by steamer to and from any part of the constituency of the member and any other part of his`
  line `constituency or the nearest port in the main land of India; ^6[or]`
  line
  line `(ii) to one free non-transferable pass for the spouse, if any, of the member to travel by the`
  line `highest class by steamer to and from the usual place of residence of the member in his`
  line `constituency and the nearest port in the main land of India,`
  line `^7[at any time between the Island and`
  line `the main land of India; and]`
  line
  line `^8[(iii) to an amount equal to the fare by air either for the spouse, if any, of the member or for`
  line `one person to accompany the member from the usual place of residence in the Island to the`
  line `nearest airport of the main land of India ^9[and back]:`
  line
  line `Provided that nothing in this sub-section shall be construed as absolving the person accompanying`
  line `the member or the spouse of the member from payment of any diet charges payable by such person or`
  line `spouse during such travel.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 29 of 1972, s. 4 (w.e.f. 9-6-1972).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 60 of 1988, s. 5, for the opening paragraph (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 30 of 1989, s. 2 (w.e.f. 28-8-1989).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by Act 60 of 1988, s. 5, for "a free steamer pass issued to a member" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `5. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "lowest class" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by s. 5, ibid., for "and" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 60 of 1988, s. 5, for "once during every session" (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `8. Ins. by s. 5, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `9. Ins. by Act 30 of 1989, s. 2 (w.e.f. 28-8-1989).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_aa:
  sectionId (10757)
  sectionNo 6AA
  orderNo 9
  title `Special facility to members from Ladakh.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_aa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_aa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10757&sectionno=6AA&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_6_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[6AA. Special facility to members from Ladakh.--(1) Without prejudice to the provisions of`
  line `section 6, every member who has his ordinary place of residence in the Ladakh area of the State of`
  line `Jammu and Kashmir* shall be entitled to an amount equal to the fare by air for each single journey by`
  line `air performed by him from any airport in Ladakh to the airport in Delhi and back at any time.`
  line
  line `(2) In addition to the air travel provided to a member under sub-section (1), he shall also be`
  line `entitled to an amount equal to the fare by air for each single journey by air performed by the spouse, if`
  line `any, of the member or one person to accompany such member, from any airport in Ladakh area to the`
  line `airport in Delhi and back at any time.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_aa_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 60 of 1988, s. 6 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `*. Vide notification No. S.O. 3912(E), dated 30th October, 2019, this Act is made applicable to the Union territory of Jammu`
  line `and Kashmir and the Union territory of Ladakh.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_b:
  sectionId (10758)
  sectionNo 6B
  orderNo 10
  title `Travel facilities to members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10758&sectionno=6B&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_6_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[6B. Travel facilities to members.--^2[(1)] Without prejudice to the other provisions of this Act,`
  line `Act, every member shall be entitled to--`
  line
  line `(i) one free air-conditioned two-tier class railway pass for one person to accompany the`
  line `member when he travels by rail; and`
  line
  line `(ii) free travel by any railway in India in first class air-conditioned or executive class in any`
  line `train with the spouse, if any, of the member from any place in India to any other place in India`
  line `and if such journey or part thereof is performed by air, from any place other than usual place of`
  line `residence of the member, to Delhi and back, to an amount equal to the fare by air for such journey`
  line `or part thereof or the amount equal to the journey performed by air from the usual place of the`
  line `residence of the member to Delhi and back, whichever is less:]`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that where a member has no spouse, such member may be accompanied by any person`
  line `person in place of the spouse, and notwithstanding anything containing in clause (i), the person so`
  line `accompanying shall be entitled to every facility available to the spouse.]`
  line
  line `^4[(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in clause (ii) of sub-section (1), the spouse of a Member`
  line `Member shall be entitled to travel,--`
  line
  line `(a) any number of times, by railway in first class air-conditioned or executive class in any`
  line `train from the usual place of residence of the Member to Delhi and back; and`
  line
  line `(b) when Parliament is in session, by air or partly by air and partly by rail, from the usual`
  line `place of residence of the Member to Delhi or back, subject to the condition that the total number`
  line `of such air journeys shall not exceed eight in a year:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any such journey or part thereof is performed by air from any place other`
  line `than the usual place of residence of the Member to Delhi and back, then, such spouse shall be entitled`
  line `to an amount equal to the fare by air for such journey or part thereof, as the case may be, or to the amount equal to the journey performed by air from the usual place of residence of the Member to`
  line `Delhi and back, whichever is less.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 16 of 1999, s. 4, for section 6B (w.e.f. 22-3-1999).`
  line
  line `2. Section 6B renumbered as sub-section (1) by Act 17 of 2000, s. 3 (w.e.f. 7-6-2000).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 3, ibid. (w.e.f. 7-6-2000).`
  line
  line `64. Subs. by Act 37 of 2010, s. 4, for sub-section (2) (w.e.f. 1-10-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_c:
  sectionId (10759)
  sectionNo 6C
  orderNo 11
  title `Air travel facilities in certain circumstances.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 105 of 1976, s. 6, (w.e.f. 9-9-1976).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10759&sectionno=6C&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_6_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[6C. Air travel facilities in certain circumstances.--Without prejudice to the other provisions`
  line `of this Act, where during any part of a year the usual place of residence of a member in his`
  line `constituency is inaccessible to or from any place outside his constituency by road. rail or steamer due`
  line `to climatic conditions, but there is air service between any place in his constituency, and the nearest`
  line `place, having rail service, outside his constituency, such member shall be entitled to travel to and from`
  line `by air from the nearest place in his constituency where there is air service to such place having rail`
  line `service:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the nearest place having air service is outside his constituency, such member`
  line `shall be entitled to travel to and from by air only from such place to the nearest place having rail`
  line service.]
obj_root_law_sections_6_d:
  sectionId (10760)
  sectionNo 6D
  orderNo 12
  title `Special facilities to blind and physically incapacitated Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_d_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_d_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10760&sectionno=6D&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_6_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[6D. Special facilities to blind and physically incapacitated Members.--A member who is`
  line `blind or who is, in the opinion of the Chairman of the Council of States or, as the case may be, the`
  line `Speaker of the House of the People, so incapacitated physically as to require the facility of an`
  line `attendant shall, with respect to each such journey--`
  line
  line `(i) by air as is referred to in clause (b) of sub-section (1) of section 4 or clause (b) of`
  line `sub-section (1) or sub-section (2) of section 5 or section 6C which he performs along with an`
  line `attendant be entitled (in addition to the allowances which he is entitled under section 4 or section`
  line `5 or, as the case may be, section 6C) to an amount equal to one fare by air for such journey;`
  line
  line `(ii) by rail as is referred to in section 4, section 5, section 6 or section 6B be allowed the`
  line `facility of the one free railway pass for an attendant, to attend such member, in the same class in`
  line `which such member travels in lieu of one free air-conditioned two-tier class railway pass under`
  line `clause (i) of sub-section (1) of section 6B.]`
  line
  line `^2[(iii) by road as is referred to in section 4 or section 5, be entitled to an amount equal to one`
  line `road mileage.]`
obj_root_law_sections_6_d_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 17 of 2000, s. 4, for section 6D (w.e.f.7-6-2000).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 40 of 2006, s. 5 (w.e.f. 17-5-2004).`
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (10761)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 13
  title `Allowances during short intervals between the termination of one session and the commencement of another session, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10761&sectionno=7&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `^1[Where the intervals between the adjournment of a House`
  line `House of Parliament or, as the case may be, one sitting of a committee and the re-assembly of that`
  line `House or the next sitting of the committee at the same place] does not exceed ^2[five days] and the`
  line `member concerned elects to remain at such place during the interval, he shall be entitled to draw for`
  line `each day of residence at such place a daily allowance at the rate specified in section 3:`
  line
  line `Provided that, if the member leaves such place during the interval, his absence from the place`
  line `shall be treated as absence during a session of a House of Parliament or a sitting of the committee, as`
  line `the case may be, and the provisions of section 5 shall apply accordingly.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 55 of 1958, s. 6, for "Where the interval between the termination of one session of a House of`
  line `Parliament or, as the case may be, one sitting of a committee and the commencement of another session or sitting at`
  line `the same place" (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 40 of 2006, s. 6, for seven days (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (10762)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 14
  title `Constituency allowance and amenities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10762&sectionno=8&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `^1[8. Constituency allowance and amenities.--A member shall be entitled to such constituency`
  line `allowance ^2[office expense allowance] and to such medical facilities for himself and for members of`
  line `his family and to such housing, telephone, water, electricity facilities or such amount in cash in lieu of`
  line `all or any of such facilities, as may be prescribed by rules under section 9:]`
  line
  line `^3[Provided that where the House of the People is sooner dissolved before completing five years`
  line `from the date appointed for its first meeting, the member of such House may be allowed without payment, to such extent of the quota of free telephone calls or free units of electricity or free units in`
  line `kilolitres of water, available to him for a year in which such dissolution of such House takes place, as`
  line `remains unutilised on the date of such dissolution, to avail during the period commencing on and from`
  line `the date of such dissolution and ending on the date immediately preceding the date on which the`
  line `notification under section 73 of the Representation of the People Act, 1951 (43 of 1951) has been`
  line `issued for the constitution of subsequent House of the People subject to the condition that such`
  line `Member shall be liable to pay for any telephone calls, in excess of the calls so allowed to be made`
  line `during such period on the telephone provided to him by the Government for such purpose, and units`
  line `of electricity or kilolitres of water consumed in excess of the free electricity or kilolitres of water`
  line `allowed:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where the member referred to in the first proviso becomes member of the`
  line `subsequent House of the People as referred to be constituted in that proviso, then, he shall be entitled`
  line `for the adjustment of the excess telephone calls, units of electricity, kilolitres of water for the payment`
  line `of which he is liable under the first proviso against the quota of free telephone calls, units of`
  line `electricity and kilolitres of water for which he is entitled during the first year of the duration of such`
  line `subsequent House of the People.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 74 of 1985, s. 5, for section 8 (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 60 of 1988, s. 8 (w.e.f. 1-4-1988).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 17 of 2000, s. 5 (w.e.f. 26-4-1999).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a:
  sectionId (10763)
  sectionNo 8A
  orderNo 15
  title Pension.
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10763&sectionno=8A&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_content:
  string
  line `^1[8A. Pension.--^2[(1) With effect from the 18th day of May, 2009, there shall be paid a pension`
  line `of ^3[twenty five thousand rupees] per mensem to every person who has served for any period as a`
  line `Member of the Provisional Parliament or either House of Parliament:`
  line
  line `Provided that where a person has served as a Member of the Provisional Parliament or either`
  line `House of Parliament for a period exceeding five years, there shall be paid to him an additional`
  line `pension of ^4[two thousand rupees ] per mensem for every year served in excess of five years.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purpose of this sub-section, "Provisional Parliament" shall include the`
  line `body which functioned as the Constituent Assembly of the Dominion of India immediately before the`
  line `commencement of the Constitution.]`
  line
  line `^5[(1A) The pension and additional pension to every person shall be increased after every five years`
  line `years commencing from 1st April, 2023 on the basis of Cost Inflation Index provided under clause (v)`
  line `of Explanation to section 48 of the Income-tax Act, 1961 (43 of 1961).]`
  line
  line `^6* * * * *`
  line
  line `(2) Where any person entitled to pension under sub-section (1),--`
  line
  line `(i) is elected to the office of the President or Vice-President or is appointed to the office of the`
  line `Governor of any State or the Administrator of any Union territory; or`
  line
  line `(ii) becomes a member of the Council of States or the House of the People or any Legislative`
  line `Assembly of a State or Union territory or any Legislative Council of a State or the Metropolitan`
  line `Council of Delhi constituted under section 3 of the Delhi Administration Act, 1966 (19 of 1966);`
  line or
  line
  line `(iii) is employed on a salary under the Central Government or any State Government or any`
  line `corporation owned or controlled by the Central Government or any State Government, or any`
  line `local authority or becomes otherwise entitled to any remuneration from such Government,`
  line `corporation or local authority,`
  line
  line `such person shall not be entitled to any pension under sub-section (1) for the period during which he`
  line `continues to hold such office or as such member, or is so employed, or continues to be entitled to such`
  line `remuneration:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the salary payable to such person for holding such office or being such`
  line `member or so employed, or where the remuneration referred to in clause (iii) payable to such person,`
  line `is, in either case, less than the pension payable to him under sub-section (1), such person shall be`
  line `entitled only to receive the balance as pension under that sub-section.`
  line
  line `^7[(3) Where any person entitled to pension under sub-section (1) is also entitled to any other`
  line `pension, such person shall be entitled to receive the pension under sub-section (1) in addition to such`
  line `other pension.]`
  line
  line `(4) In computing the number of years, for the purposes of sub-section (1), the period during which`
  line `a person has served as a Minister as defined in the Salaries and Allowances of Ministers Act, 1952`
  line `(58 of 1952) or ^8[as an officer of Parliament] as defined in the Salaries and Allowances of Officers of`
  line `Parliament Act,1953 (20 of 1953), (other than the Chairman of the Council of States) ^9[or as a Leader`
  line `of the Opposition as defined in the Salary and Allowances of Leaders of Opposition in Parliament`
  line `Act, 1977 (33 of 1977), or has served in all or any two of such capacities] by virtue of his membership`
  line `in the House of the People or in the Council of States shall also be taken into account.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_a_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 105 of 1976, s. 7 (w.e.f. 9-9-1976).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 37 of 2010, s. 5, for sub-section (1) (w.e.f. 1-10-2010).`
  line
  line `3. Subs. by Act 13 of 2018, s.144, for "twenty thousand rupees" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `4. Subs. by s, 144, ibid., for "fifteen hundred rupees" (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by s.144, ibid. (w.e.f. 1-4-2018).`
  line
  line `6. Sub-section (1A) and the Explanation thereunder omitted by Act 40 of 2006, s. 7 (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
  line
  line `7. Subs. by Act 48 of 1993, s. 4, for sub-section (3) (w.e.f. 9-6-1993).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 33 of 1977, s. 11, for "an officer of Parliament" (w.e.f. 1-11-1977).`
  line
  line `9. Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for "or both" (w.e.f. 1-11-1977).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_aa:
  sectionId (10764)
  sectionNo 8AA
  orderNo 16
  title `Travel facility to ex-Members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_aa_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_aa_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10764&sectionno=8AA&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_8_aa_content:
  string
  line `^1[8AA. Travel facility to ex-Members.-- ^2[(1)] Every person who is not a sitting Member but`
  line `has served for any period as a Member of either House of Parliament shall be,--`
  line
  line `(a) with effect from the 18th day of January, 1999, entitled along with a companion to travel`
  line `in any train by any railway in India in air-conditioned two-tier class; or`
  line
  line `(b) entitled to travel alone in any train by any railway in India in air-conditioned first class,`
  line
  line `without payment of any charges on the basis of an authorisation issued for this purpose by the`
  line `Secretariat of either House of Parliament, as the case may be.]`
  line
  line `^3[(2) Every person who is not a sitting member but has served for any period as a member from`
  line `the Andaman and Nicobar Islands or the Lakshadweep, shall be entitled to travel by the highest class`
  line `of accommodation in any steamer sailing between the Andaman and Nicobar Islands or, as the case`
  line `may be, the Lakshadweep and the main land territory of India in addition to the facilities available to`
  line `such member under sub-section (1), without payment of any charges on the basis of an authorisation`
  line `issued for this purpose by the Secretariat of either House of Parliament.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_aa_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Subs. by Act 9 of 2004, s. 7, for section 8AA (w.e.f. 9-1-2004).`
  line
  line `2. Section 8AA numbered as sub-section (1) by Act 40 of 2006, s. 8 (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by s. 8, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_ab:
  sectionId (10765)
  sectionNo 8AB
  orderNo 17
  title `Rounding off period of pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_ab_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 9 of 2004, s. 8 (w.e.f. 9-1-2004).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10765&sectionno=8AB&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_8_ab_content:
  string
  line `^1[8AB. Rounding off period of pension.--Where the period for which the pension is payable`
  line `under this Act contains a part of a year, then, if such part is nine months or more, it shall be reckoned`
  line `equivalent to complete one year for the purpose of payment of additional pension under sub-section`
  line `(1) of section 8A and if such part is less than nine months, it shall be ignored.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_ac:
  sectionId (10766)
  sectionNo 8AC
  orderNo 18
  title `Family pension.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_ac_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_ac_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10766&sectionno=8AC&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_8_ac_content:
  string
  line `^1[8AC. Family pension.--(1) On the death of a member of either House of Parliament during his`
  line `term of office, his spouse, if any, or dependent of such member shall be paid during the remaining`
  line `period of life of such spouse or, as the case may be, such dependent so long as such dependent`
  line `continues to be a dependent within the meaning of clause (aa) of section 2, family pension equivalent`
  line `to one-half of the pension which such member of Parliament would have received had he retired:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such family pension shall be payable to a dependent if such dependent is a sitting`
  line `member of Parliament or is drawing pension under section 8A.`
  line
  line `(2) The family pension payable under sub-section (1) shall also be payable to the spouse or`
  line `dependent of a person who was a member of either House of Parliament or the Provisional Parliament`
  line `at any time ^2*** and died after serving as such member:`
  line
  line `Provided that such spouse or dependent is not drawing any pension under this Act or is not`
  line `entitled to draw family pension under the proviso to sub-section (1):`
  line
  line `Provided further that no person shall be entitled to claim arrears of any family pension under this`
  line `sub-section in respect of a period before the commencement of the Salary, Allowances and Pension of`
  line `Members of Parliament (Amendment) Act, 2006 (40 of 2006).`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- For the purposes of this section, "Provisional Parliament" shall include the body`
  line `which functioned as the Constituent Assembly of the Dominion of India immediately before the`
  line `commencement of the Constitution.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_ac_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 40 of 2006, s. 9 (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
  line
  line `2. The words, brackets and figures "before the commencement of the Salary, Allowances and Pension of Members of`
  line `Parliament (Amendment) Act, 2006 (40 of 2006)" omitted by Act 13 of 2018, s. 145 (w.e.f. 15-9-2006).`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b:
  sectionId (10767)
  sectionNo 8B
  orderNo 19
  title `Advances for purchase of conveyance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_b_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10767&sectionno=8B&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[8B. Advances for purchase of conveyance.--There may be paid to a member by way of repayable advance such sum of money not exceeding ^2[four lakh rupees] as may be determined by rules`
  line `made in this behalf under section 9 for the purchase of a conveyance.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8_b_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 74 of 1985, s. 7 (w.e.f. 26-12-1985).`
  line
  line `2. Subs. by Act 37 of 2010, s. 6, for "one lakh rupees" (w.e.f. 1-10-2010).`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (10768)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 20
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476&sectionId=10768&sectionno=9&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_33_52_00003_195430_1517807322476
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) For the purpose of making rules under this section, there shall be`
  line `constituted a Joint Committee of both Houses of Parliament consisting of five members from the`
  line `Council of States nominated by the Chairman and ten members from the House of the People`
  line `nominated by the Speaker.`
  line
  line `(2) The Joint Committee constituted under sub-section (1) shall elect its Chairman and shall have`
  line `power to regulate its procedure.`
  line
  line ^1
  line `[(2A) A member of the Joint Committee shall hold office as such member for one year from the`
  line `date of his nomination and any casual vacancy in the Joint Committee may be filled by nomination by`
  line `the Chairman of the Council of States or the Speaker of the House of the People, as the case may be.`
  line
  line `Explanation.-- In the case of a member of a Joint Committee holding office as such immediately`
  line `before the commencement of the Salaries and Allowances of Members of Parliament (Amendment)`
  line `Act, 1958 (55 of 1958), the period of one year shall be computed from the date of such`
  line commencement.]
  line
  line `(3) The Joint Committee constituted under sub-section (1) may ^1`
  line `[after consultation with the`
  line `Central Government] make rules to provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the routes for the performance of any journey;`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(aa) the person who may be specified as dependent under sub-clause (g) of clause (aa) of`
  line `section 2;]`
  line
  line `(b) the manner in which fractions of a day shall be dealt with for the purpose of determining`
  line `the daily allowance admissible for that day;`
  line
  line `(c) the travelling allowance admissible where a member is provided with free transit for the`
  line `whole or any part of a journey ^1`
  line `[and the reduction of the daily allowance where a member is`
  line `provided with free board or lodging at the expense of the Government or a local authority];`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(cc) the date at which road mileage shall be paid under sub-clause (ii) of clause (c) of`
  line `sub-section (1) of section 4;]`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ccc) the transit accommodation and the period for which such accommodation may be`
  line `provided under section 5A;]`
  line
  line `(d) the travelling allowance admissible where the place from which a member commences his`
  line `journey or to which he returns is not his usual place of residence;`
  line
  line ^4
  line `[(dd) the travelling allowance admissible in respect of journeys performed by any vessel`
  line `where there is no regular steamer service;`
  line
  line `(ddd) the travelling and daily allowances admissible for journeys performed by a member in`
  line `the course of a tour outside India undertaken in connection with his duties as such member;]`
  line
  line `(e) the form in which certificates, if any, shall be furnished by a member for the purpose of`
  line `claiming any allowance under this Act;`
  line
  line ^5
  line `[(ee) the form in which certificates, if any, shall be furnished by any person for the purpose`
  line `of claiming any pension under this Act;]`
  line
  line ^6
  line `[(f) the constituency allowance and medical and other facilities mentioned in section 8 and`
  line `the amount to be paid in cash in lieu of such facilities;`
  line
  line `(ff) the amount which may be paid by way of repayable advance for the purchase of`
  line `conveyance; the rate of interest thereon and the mode of recovery of such amount and interest`
  line `thereon; and]`
  line
  line ^7
  line `[(fff) to provide for carry forward of unutilised free telephone calls pertaining to any year`
  line `beginning on or after the 1st day of April, 2002 to any subsequent year;]`
  line
  line `(g) generally for regulating the payment of ^8`
  line `[daily and travelling allowances and pension]`
  line `under this Act].`
  line
  line `(4) Any rules made under sub-section (3) shall not take effect until they are approved and`
  line `confirmed by the Chairman of the Council of States and the Speaker of the House of the People and`
  line `are published in the Official Gazette, and such publication of the rules shall be conclusive proof that`
  line `they have been duly made.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line `1. Ins. by Act 55 of 1958, s. 8 (w.e.f.30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `2. Ins. by Act 9 of 2004, s. 9 (w.e.f. 9-1-2004).`
  line
  line `3. Ins. by Act 61 of 1982, s. 4 (w.e.f. 6-11-1982).`
  line
  line `4. Ins. by Act 55 of 1958, s. 8 (w.e.f. 30-12-1958).`
  line
  line `5. Ins. by Act 105 of 1976, s. 8 (w.e.f. 9-9-1976).`
  line
  line `6. Subs. by Act 74 of 1985, s. 8, for "clause (f)" (w.e.f.26-12-1985).`
  line
  line `7. Ins. by Act 9 of 2004, s. 9 (w.e.f. 9-1-2004).`
  line
  line `8. Subs. by Act 105 of 1976, s. 8, for "daily and travelling allowances" ( w.e.f. 9-9-1976).`
